# Bounded Context Rules

## BC1 — Intake & Reconciliation
- IntakeWorkers fetch and validate; ReconciliationEngine materializes canonical entities.
- IdentityService resolves external IDs; fuzzy-below-threshold → quarantine only.
- CorrectionPipeline replays analyst overrides with ANALYST_OVERRIDE authority.

## BC2 — Official Qualification
- Triggered only by `MatchResultLockedEvent` (never live scores).
- Output: immutable `QualificationSnapshot` with `engineVersion` and `inputHash`.
- Promoted from `src/lib/qualification.ts` — logic unchanged, context moved to server.

## BC3 — Prediction & Scenario
- Dixon-Coles + factor attribution; scenario workspaces are ephemeral (Redis TTL 24h).
- `simulateTournament` must be seeded and deterministic for bookmarking.
- Factor weights configurable via DB; attribution is post-hoc wrapper on core model.

## Cross-context
- Never import BC3 from BC2 or BC1 business paths.
- UI must render official status (BC2) and prediction status (BC3) in separate visual regions.
